Bulgogi

3 c water
2 c shoyu
2 c white sugar
1/2 c sesame oil
1/2 tbsp garlic powder
1/2 tbsp onion powder
1/2 tbsp korean red pepper flakes + more for garnish
2 lbs rib eye steaks, thinly sliced crosswise to 1/2" slices
2 tbsp vegetable oil
thinly sliced scallions for garnish
toasted white and black sesame seeds for garnish

In a large bowl whisk together the water, shoyu, sugar, sesame oil, garlic and onion pwders, and korean red pepper flakes until the sugar has dissolved. Add  the sliced rib eye and let marinate for 1 hr. In a large cast iron pan, heat the vegetable oil over high heat. Drain the meat, discarding the marinade. Working in batches, cook the meat, flipping once, until caramelized and golden, 1 min per side. Transfer to a platter and garnish with scallions, sesame seeds, and more pepper flakes.
